Art Nouveau: The Style of the 1890s

Octopus Books | 1972 | ISBN: 0907408141 | English | 166 pages | PDF | 33.6 MB


This authoritative guide contains 92 full colour illustrations that show brilliant examples of Art Nouveau's precursors and the style itself as it was applied in painting, architecture, sculpture, stained glass, ceramics, and small-scale domestic objects
